text.tspan: Monthly confirmed cases of influenza, non-sentinel surveillance
Non-sentinel surveillance includes data from multiple sources, including outbreak investigation, universal
testing, and testing at the point of care. Only a fraction of potential cases of influenza are tested by labs to
confirm whether they have influenza and to identify their strain. The level of testing may vary between countries
Data source: FluNet by the World Health Organization (2023)
Note: This includes confirmed cases of all influenza strains.
